dfu-programmer
------------------------------------------
dfu-programmer is an implementation of the Device Firmware Upgrade class USB
driver that enables firmware upgrades for various USB enabled (with the correct
bootloader) Atmel chips. This program was created because the Atmel 'FLIP'
program for flashing devices does not support flashing via USB on Linux, and
because standard DFU loaders do not work for Atmel's chips.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.0-0.450.g2ef627c46eb2
  libusb1.0-1.0.21-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.41-3
  cygport-0.36.7-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  libusb1.0-devel-1.0.21-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/dfu-programmer/dfu-programmer

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/dfu-programmer/dfu-programmer/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack dfu-programmer-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./dfu-programmer-1.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/dfu-programmer-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/dfu-programmer-1.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(dfu-programmer)
  /usr/bin/dfu-programmer.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/dfu-programmer.README
  /usr/share/doc/dfu-programmer/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/dfu-programmer/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/dfu-programmer/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/dfu-programmer/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/dfu-programmer.1.gz

